Use window functions:

    select seller_id, seller_name, category_name, cnt
    from (select seller_id, seller_name, category_name, count(*) as cnt,
                 row_number() over (partition by seller_id, seller_name order by count(*) desc) as seqnum
          from t
          group by seller_id, seller_name, category_name
         ) ssc
    where seqnum = 1;

Note that in the event of ties, this returns an arbitrary highest value.  If you want all of them, use `rank()` instead of `row_number()`.

